    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Tamás Nádasdy (Vienna, 26 May 1552)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>The councillors of the Chamber are making a mistake when they are not
                            sending Tamás Nádasdy his money when they should. Maurice, Elector of
                            Saxony has occupied Udine through deceit, forgetting about his faith and
                            office; the Emperor still holds Ulm and Augsburg. Albert Alcibiades has
                            accepted the capitulation of Nuremberg, he is said to have burned down
                            the surrounding area almost completely. The French King advanced to
                            Speyer, but when he heard there that a city in Lorraine was under
                            attack, he retreated to liberate that city. When the Emperor heard about
                            the occupation of Udine, he traveled to Bruneck. The King is
                            accompanying the Bishop of Trento to Padua, and they are expecting
                            Maurice to come there to negotiate.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Servitiorum meorum commendationem, Spectabilis Magnifice Domine et
                    Frater Observandissime! </p>
                <p>Domini camerarii male habeant, quod <choice>
                        <orig><gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/>niam</orig>
                        <supplied><corr>pecu</corr>niam</supplied>
                    </choice> Dominationi Vestrae non miserint, <choice>
                        <orig><gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/>ent</orig>
                        <supplied><corr>deb</corr>ent</supplied>
                    </choice> tamen, si vera sunt, quae dicunt. <choice>
                        <orig><gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/>ova</orig>
                        <supplied><corr>N</corr>ova</supplied>
                    </choice> haec sunt. <persName>Dux Mauritius</persName><note type="critic"
                        >Maurice, Elector of Saxony.</note>
                    <choice>
                        <orig>f<gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/>i</orig>
                        <supplied>f<corr>ide</corr>i</supplied>
                    </choice> et officii sui immemor, <placeName>Clusam</placeName><note
                        type="critic">Probably Udine.</note> arcem regiae maiestatis ad ostium
                    Tyrolis versus <placeName>Augustam</placeName><note type="critic"
                        >Augsburg.</note> existentem astu nuper accepit, <placeName>Ulma</placeName>
                    et <placeName>Argentina</placeName><note type="critic">Strasbourg.</note>
                    strenue et constanter in fide caesaris permansit. <persName>Marchio
                        Albertus</persName><note type="critic">Albert Alcibiades, Margrave of
                        Brandenburg-Kulmbach (1522–1557).</note> nebulo ille et omnium bonorum
                    suorum decoctor <choice>
                        <orig>civit<gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/>em</orig>
                        <supplied>civit<corr>at</corr>em</supplied>
                    </choice> quandam Newrembergensium per <choice>
                        <orig><gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/>ditionem</orig>
                        <supplied><corr>de</corr>ditionem</supplied>
                    </choice> accepit. Dicunt eum <choice>
                        <orig>alio<gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/></orig>
                        <supplied>alio<corr>qui</corr></supplied>
                    </choice> suburbii civitatis quoque Newrembergensis <choice>
                        <orig>p<gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/></orig>
                        <supplied>p<corr>aene</corr></supplied>
                    </choice> combussisse. <persName>Rex Galliae</persName><note type="critic"
                        >Francis I of France.</note>
                    <choice>
                        <orig><gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/>gressus</orig>
                        <supplied><corr>in</corr>gressus</supplied>
                    </choice> fuit <placeName>Spyram</placeName><note type="critic">Speier.</note>
                    usque. <choice>
                        <orig>Illin<gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/></orig>
                        <supplied>Illin<corr>c</corr></supplied>
                    </choice> audita obsidione cuiusdam <choice>
                        <orig>civi<gap extent="unknown" reason="damage" unit="word"/>s</orig>
                        <supplied>civi<corr>tati</corr>s</supplied>
                    </choice> in Lotharingia, quam in manibus suis habet per exercitum Flandricum
                    serenissimae reginae facta et etiam unius vel alterius civitatis occupatione
                    penes <placeName>Rhenum</placeName><note type="critic">Rhine river.</note>
                    retrocessisse dicitur, ad liberandam ab obsidione civitatem illam.
                        <persName>Maiestas caesarea</persName> audita <placeName>Clusae</placeName>
                    captione, profecta est ad civitatem quandam cuius nomen nunc non succurrit, <add
                        corresp="Olahus" type="insert">opinor Prawnek</add>.<note type="critic"
                        >Bruneck.</note>
                    <!--<persName/>-->Tridentini <choice>
                        <orig><gap extent="1" reason="damage" unit="word"/>dinalis</orig>
                        <supplied><corr>car</corr>dinalis</supplied>
                    </choice><note type="critic">Cristoforo Madruzzo (1512–1578) studied at the
                        University of Padua and Bologna. He first received the canonry at Trento in
                        1529. In 1536, he was Canon of Salzburg, in 1537 Canon of Brixen, and
                        following Bernhard von Cles’s death, he earned the archiepiscopate of
                        Trento, see <hi rend="smallcap">Becker</hi>, 2006.</note>
                    <milestone unit="pb"/> ad <placeName>Brixinam</placeName>,<note type="critic"
                        >Brixen.</note> quattuor millionibus distantium <del corresp="Olahus"
                        >profecta est</del> maiestas regia comitata est eum aliquamdiu, et hodie,
                    uti credimus, constituetur <placeName>Patavii</placeName>.<note type="critic"
                        >Padua.</note> Exspectamus <persName>Mauritium</persName> et alios eo, si
                    venerint ad tractatus faciendos. <del corresp="Olahus">Dux Ioannes</del> Illic
                    sua maiestas mox revertetur. <persName>Dux Ioannes</persName> captivus Saxoniae
                    est <gap extent="1" reason="illegible" unit="word"/> donatus est tamen in curam
                    caesaris. Haec sunt, quae habeo. Dominatio Vestra feliciter valeat.</p>
                <p>Ex <placeName>Vienna</placeName> 26. Maii 1552.</p>
                <p>
                    <seg type="signature">Frater et servitor Agriensis etc. manu propria</seg>
                </p>
                <p>Serenissimus <persName>Maximilianus</persName> rex de rebus nonnullis
                    nuntiavit per dominum <persName>Bathyany</persName><note type="critic">Kristóf
                        Batthyány.</note> Dominationi Vestrae. Ad has exspectamus responsum.</p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p>Spectabili et magnifico domino Thomae de Nadasd, comiti perpetuo
                    terrae Fogaras, iudici curiae regiae maiestatis et supremo regni capitaneo etc.
                    domino et fratri observandissimo.</p>
                <p>Ad manus proprias.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
